1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,502
Open Margin Sentinel. This is a local reviewer demo with real clicks and real UI state changes.

2
00:00:05,502 --> 00:00:10,193
Click Run profit scan. The dashboard moves from ready state to scanning and then shows real findings.

3
00:00:10,193 --> 00:00:18,710
After the scan, the Action center shows catalog health, issues to review, and inventory risk.

4
00:00:18,710 --> 00:00:28,174
Click the Fix first card to open the priority finding and suggested minimum price.

5
00:00:28,174 --> 00:00:39,113
Click a finding row. The table highlights the selected product and keeps price, cost, margin, risk, and suggested price visible.

6
00:00:39,113 --> 00:00:46,594
Open Import costs. Merchants can use variant ID, inventory item ID, or SKU plus cost.

7
00:00:46,594 --> 00:00:56,556
Click Download variant cost template. This is useful when SKUs are missing or inconsistent.

8
00:00:56,556 --> 00:01:01,506
Click Preview / import costs. The app matches CSV rows to Shopify variants before saving.

9
00:01:01,506 --> 00:01:11,008
The import preview now shows matched rows, saved costs, warnings, and margin impact.

10
00:01:11,008 --> 00:01:18,914
Open What-if. This models supplier cost increases before low-margin products keep selling.

11
00:01:18,914 --> 00:01:23,845
Click Run what-if. The scenario recalculates at-risk SKUs and inventory risk.

12
00:01:23,845 --> 00:01:33,348
The what-if result shows new at-risk SKUs, added inventory risk, and next actions by product.

13
00:01:33,348 --> 00:01:41,794
Open Pricing. Plans are clear: Free, Starter, and Growth.

14
00:01:41,794 --> 00:01:52,715
Click Start 14-day trial on Starter. In production, this opens Shopify managed billing.

15
00:01:52,715 --> 00:01:58,638
Close the billing preview and return to the app.

16
00:01:58,638 --> 00:02:06,614
Open Export. Merchants can download a team-ready CSV fix list.

17
00:02:06,614 --> 00:02:16,581
Click Download CSV. This generates a saved findings export without changing Shopify prices.

18
00:02:16,581 --> 00:02:25,583
The export includes issue type, product, cost source, margin gap, inventory risk, suggested price, and next action.

19
00:02:25,583 --> 00:02:34,084
Final reviewer takeaway: Margin Sentinel finds margin leaks, explains what to fix first, and remains read-only.

20
00:02:34,084 --> 00:02:46,086
This walkthrough covered the required review path: dashboard, finding details, supplier import, what-if, pricing, and export.

21
00:02:46,086 --> 00:02:58,088
The important behavior is visible: buttons change state, results appear after clicks, and export confirms a generated download.

22
00:02:58,088 --> 00:03:10,090
Margin Sentinel recommends actions, but merchants stay in control of price and supplier cost changes.
